{
  "stem": "10587.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And-- and everyone-- he purposefully walk-- walked diagonally through the main square, so that everyone would bow and-- and hold their hat and say, Good Shabbat, Mr.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Enoch.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Good Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And he was well-known in the community, and was also a big man, and-- and quite a showman.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So-- In the temple, they used to sit on the western wall, only he and his son, which lived in the same building.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And-- and the son-in-laws, and-- like my father and other husbands from-- of my aunts.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It really was a very nice little Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "There was quite a few Jewish people that lived in Oswiecim.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And this-- unfortunately in 1941, this-- the community stopped to exist.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my brother and I used to be very close.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "My younger brother and I used to be very close.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And we would [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] horse around as much as we could, all day long.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But we did study quite hard as well, because we went to Polish school in the morning, to the cheder in afternoon, and my parents insisted that we do our homework.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "So we played hard and we also studied hard.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] When the war broke out, the-- the Germans occupied Poland in I believe September of 1939.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "They didn't have far to go to find Oswiecim because we were right very close to the German border.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And a few weeks later, they renamed the main square where I lived to Adolf Hitler's Platz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And the town was renamed back to Auschwitz, which at one time, I believe, must have been Auschwitz, the name of Auschwitz during the time when-- when Auschwitz was part of Austria.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were six siblings.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My oldest brother, his name is Herman.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
